people.name: Gustavus Donald Pearson
people.notes: Joined Canadian Navy in 1942, stationed in Halifax/Sidney NS and St. John NF. Was educated in Winnipeg, and while studying accounting at business college he joined Hagborg Fuel. In 1954 he became a manufacturers agent representing firms in Canada, the United States, and England. As a young man Don was member of the Order of the Demolay, Winnipeg Junior Chamber of Commerce and Kildonan Canoe Club. Don was a member of the board of the Central YMCA and a longtime member of the Northwest Commercial Travellers. Don was an active Mason, first with the Fort Garry Lodge, then as a founding member of the Gateway Lodge. He later joined the Friendship Lodge and was Master in 1956. He was also a member of the Scottish Rite Bethesda Chapter Rose Croix. He was a member of the Granite Curling Club and the Wildewood Club where he enjoyed many years of curling and golf. Don enjoyed Toastmasters 250 for several years, and won a number of speech contests.

people.name: Hilding Vilhelm Nelson
people.notes: Have picture when a young boy As a member of the Engineering Institute of Canada he held positions as Chief Engineer for Vulcan Iron and Engineering and Bridge and Tank Co. Winnipeg. In 1962 he moved to Victoria BC and at the time of his retirement he was General Manager of Victoria Machinery Depot Co. In his active years he took part in the development of codes and standards for the Canadian Standards Association and the Canadian Institute of Steel Construction. Buried in Elmwood Cemetery Winnipeg.
